# SwiftPM build artifacts — never committed.
#
# `swift build` regenerates these per-machine from Package.swift + the
# Sources/ tree. Committing them is pure noise (binary blobs, machine-
# specific paths, mtime-coupled) AND a working-tree-churn liability —
# any local `swift build` makes `git status` 2000+ lines long.
#
# Standard SwiftPM convention — every SwiftPM package's .gitignore
# carries these. Apple's own swift-package-manager template generates
# this file on `swift package init`.
.build/
.swiftpm/
*.xcodeproj/
Package.resolved
DerivedData/
